The paper focuses on the problem of detecting malicious domains in the domain name system (DNS) using machine learning techniques. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of Heterogeneous Information Network (HIN) and metapath-based transductive classification methods also suggests a possible fit under database systems (cs.DB) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
